ğŸ§  1. React Core Concepts (Deep Dive)
ğŸ”¸ Components
React apps are made of components â€” reusable pieces of UI.

There are two types:

Functional Components â†’ function MyComponent()

Class Components â†’ mostly outdated, avoid for now

âœ… Example Functional Component:

jsx
Copy
Edit
function Greeting({ name }) {
  return <h1>Hello, {name}</h1>;
}
ğŸ”¸ Props (Passing Data)
Props = input to components.

jsx
Copy
Edit
<Greeting name="Priya" />
Output:

Copy
Edit
Hello, Priya
Props are read-only â€” you cannot modify them inside the child.

ğŸ”¸ State (useState)
State = variables that change over time and cause re-rendering.

jsx
Copy
Edit
const [count, setCount] = useState(0);
jsx
Copy
Edit
<button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>+</button>
ğŸ”¸ Lifecycle with useEffect
React calls useEffect() after render.

Fetch data

Set timers

Listen to events

jsx
Copy
Edit
useEffect(() => {
  console.log("Component mounted!");
}, []);
Cleanup example:

jsx
Copy
Edit
useEffect(() => {
  const timer = setInterval(() => console.log("Tick"), 1000);
  return () => clearInterval(timer); // clean up
}, []);
