ğŸ”— 2. REST APIs with React
ğŸ”¸ REST = Representational State Transfer
Common operations:

GET â†’ fetch data

POST â†’ send data

PUT/PATCH â†’ update data

DELETE â†’ delete data

ğŸ”¸ Using fetch() to GET Data
jsx
Copy
Edit
useEffect(() => {
  fetch("https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users")
    .then(res => res.json())
    .then(data => setUsers(data));
}, []);
